_count": 144}, "passed": true}}, "text": "Iraq--Oil: Prime Minister Qasim has deliberately deadlocked negotiations with the American, British-Dutch, and French-owned Iraq Petroleum Company (IPC), ending another round in the talks which have been carried on intermittently since the July 1958 coup which brought Qasim to power. Qasim has ordered the company to halt all oil exploration and confine its activities to producing oil in existing fields. The company already has agreed to substantial changes in its oil concession, including surrendering 90 percent of its concession area, and now apparently feels that further negotiations are impossible. Qasim is attempting to make IPC a scapegoat for the country's economic and political problems, and a vitriolic press campaign against IPC is now under way. The prime minister may carry out his often-repeated and politically popular threat to nationalize the French share of IPC as a gesture of solidarity with the Algerian rebels", "token_count": 144, "token_end_0based": 242, "token_start_0based": 99, "token_text": "iraq oil prime minister qasim has deliberately deadlocked negotiations with the american british-dutch and french-owned iraq petroleum company ipc ending another round in the talks which have been carried on intermittently since the july 1958 coup which brought qasim to power qasim has ordered the company to halt all oil exploration and confine its activities to producing oil in existing fields the company already has agreed to substantial changes in its oil concession including surrendering 90 percent of its concession area and now apparently feels that further negotiations are impossible qasim is attempting to make ipc a scapegoat for the country's economic and political problems and a vitriolic press campaign against ipc is now under way the prime minister may carry out his often-repeated and politically popular threat to nationalize the french share of ipc as a gesture of solidarity with the algerian rebels", "unr